1
00:00:03,337 --> 00:00:05,967
Daniel:
SO, I WENT FISHING THIS WEEKEND.

2
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,176
CAUGHT A HUGE STRIPED BASS.

3
00:00:09,310 --> 00:00:10,980
THIS BIG.

4
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:12,981
[ LAUGHTER ]

5
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:14,153
WE'RE HAVING IT MOUNTED
IN MY OFFICE.

6
00:00:14,182 --> 00:00:15,322
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
MR. LEWICKI?

7
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:17,019
UH, WHATEVER
YOU SAY, DOC.

8
00:00:18,186 --> 00:00:19,216
[ LAUGHTER ]

9
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,322
ALL RIGHT.

10
00:00:23,357 --> 00:00:25,987
SO, EVEN IF MY SOON-TO-BE
FORMER TEACHING ASSISTANT

11
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,196
DIDN'T ROLL OVER ON ME
LIKE A RAT IN A BAD MAFIA FLICK,

12
00:00:28,229 --> 00:00:29,999
YOU'D KNOW I WAS LYING.

13
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,000
WHY?

14
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:32,301
'CAUSE IT'S A FISH STORY.

15
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:38,013
BUT IF I WAS A BETTER LIAR,
I'D HAVE A HUGE ADVANTAGE.

16
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:41,178
STUDIES SHOW THE MOST CONVINCING
LIARS LAND THE BEST JOBS,

17
00:00:41,209 --> 00:00:44,179
MAKE THE MOST FRIENDS,
AND GET ALL THE HOT WOMEN.

18
00:00:44,212 --> 00:00:46,212
SO IF I WAS REALLY GOOD AT IT,

19
00:00:46,247 --> 00:00:49,347
WOULD THERE STILL BE A WAY
FOR YOU TO BUST ME?

20
00:00:49,383 --> 00:00:51,323
A POLYGRAPH, MAYBE.

21
00:00:51,352 --> 00:00:53,022
[ BEEPING ]

22
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,363
Kate: DID YOU DISCOVER
A MALE INTRUDER

23
00:00:54,388 --> 00:00:57,158
IN YOUR HOME LAST NIGHT?

24
00:00:57,191 --> 00:00:59,231
YES.

25
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:02,030
DO YOU KNOW THE IDENTITY
OF THIS MAN?

26
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,332
NO.

27
00:01:03,364 --> 00:01:05,104
DID YOU SEE HIS FACE?

28
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:07,173
YES.

29
00:01:07,201 --> 00:01:09,241
CAN YOU DESCRIBE IT?

30
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:12,341
NO.

31
00:01:14,108 --> 00:01:16,178
A POLYGRAPH'S
NOT A BAD TOOL,

32
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:18,380
BUT IT ONLY MEASURES
STRESS RESPONSE.

33
00:01:18,412 --> 00:01:23,352
IN THIS CLASS, WE'RE INTERESTED
IN WHAT GOES ON IN THE BRAIN.

34
00:01:23,384 --> 00:01:26,254
AND IF WE WERE TO PUT SOMEONE
IN AN fMRI MACHINE

35
00:01:26,287 --> 00:01:29,187
AND WATCH WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN THEY MAKE UP A LIE,

36
00:01:29,223 --> 00:01:31,233
WE'D SEE THEIR DORSOLATERAL
PREFRONTAL CORTEX

37
00:01:31,259 --> 00:01:33,089
LIGHT UP
LIKE A CHRISTMAS TREE...

38
00:01:33,127 --> 00:01:34,257
[ LAUGHTER ]

39
00:01:34,295 --> 00:01:37,195
...BECAUSE WE USE OUR BRAINS
WHEN WE LIE.

40
00:01:37,231 --> 00:01:40,131
WE USE OUR BRAINS
WHEN WE'RE BEING LIED TO.

41
00:01:40,168 --> 00:01:42,138
BUT...

42
00:01:42,170 --> 00:01:47,180
CAN THE BRAIN
EVER LIE TO ITSELF?

43
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,253
Max: ALL RIGHT.

44
00:01:54,282 --> 00:01:56,082
SO YOU'VE GOT OFFICE HOURS
FROM 1:00 TO 3:00,

45
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,246
AND DON'T FORGET
THE MEETING

46
00:01:57,285 --> 00:01:59,115
WITH DEAN HALEY
AND THAT HATHAWAY GUY AT 4:00.

47
00:01:59,153 --> 00:02:00,393
GET OH, OKAY. IT.

48
00:02:00,421 --> 00:02:02,391
WHAT AM I
I DON'T KNOW.ELL HIM?

49
00:02:02,423 --> 00:02:04,433
USE YOUR DORSOLATERAL
PREFRONTAL CORTEX AND
MAKE SOMETHING UP.

50
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,358
SO YOU WANT ME
TO LIE FOR YOU NOW?

51
00:02:06,394 --> 00:02:08,164
THINK OF IT AS FOR WHAT?

52
00:02:08,196 --> 00:02:10,096
FOR LANDING A NEW JOB
WHEN I FIRE YOU

53
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,270
FOR NOT GETTING ME OUT
OF THE MEETING WITH DEAN HALEY.

54
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:14,100
DOC, THAT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.

55
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:16,204
IT'S A PARADOX, LEWICKI.
IT'S NOT SUPPOSED TO.

56
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:20,269
OH, GOD! I'M SO SORRY.

57
00:02:20,308 --> 00:02:22,438
[ British accent ]
IN A BIT OF A HURRY, AREN'T WE?

58
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:24,406
I'M GONNA PAY FOR YOUR
DRY CLEANING, OKAY?

59
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:26,445
MY FAULT. I WASN'T
LOOKING WHERE I WAS GOING.

60
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,450
IN FACT, COULD WE PLEASE
MAKE THE LADY ANOTHER?

61
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,122
I INSIST.FINE.

62
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:33,251
[ SIGHS ]
CHAMOMILE TEA.

63
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:34,387
GOOD CHOICE.

64
00:02:34,422 --> 00:02:36,292
I DON'T THINK YOU NEED
ANY MORE CAFFEINE.

65
00:02:36,324 --> 00:02:38,194
ACTUALLY,
THE TEA IS FOR A FRIEND,

66
00:02:38,226 --> 00:02:40,186
AND I CAN HANDLE MY CAFFEINE
JUST FINE.

67
00:02:40,228 --> 00:02:41,198
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

68
00:02:41,229 --> 00:02:42,399
HOW ABOUT YOUR LIQUOR?

69
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:44,130
EXCUSE ME?

70
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:45,334
WELL, SEEING AS I'M
BUYING THE TEA,

71
00:02:45,366 --> 00:02:47,336
I THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU COULD BUY ME A REAL DRINK.

72
00:02:47,368 --> 00:02:49,138
7:00's GOOD FOR ME.

73
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,399
THANK YOU FOR THE TEA,

74
00:02:50,438 --> 00:02:54,378
AND AGAIN, I'M VERY SORRY
ABOUT THE SHIRT.

75
00:02:57,445 --> 00:03:00,145
Daniel: KATE.

76
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,480
WHAT, AM I ON SOME SORT
OF GOVERNMENT WATCH LIST?

77
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,176
NOT YET.

78
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:06,488
HERBAL TEA.
NO MILK, NO SUGAR.

79
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:10,491
NOW, I KNOW YOU DIDN'T
COME ALL THE WAY OVER HERE

80
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:12,264
JUST TO BRING ME TEA.

81
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:16,304
MEET FRANK
AND OLENA PRENTICE.

82
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:17,470
LOOKS LIKE
HE WON THE LOTTERY.

83
00:03:17,498 --> 00:03:19,298
ACTUALLY,
SHE COST HIM A BUNDLE.

84
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,473
MAIL-ORDER BRIDE
FROM THE UKRAINE.

85
00:03:20,501 --> 00:03:22,201
PEOPLE ACTUALLY
DO THAT?

86
00:03:22,236 --> 00:03:25,466
YEAH. WHY? ARE YOU
IN THE MARKET FOR A WIFE?

87
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:27,206
NO.

88
00:03:28,242 --> 00:03:31,212
"EASTERN BLOC
INTRODUCTIONS."

89
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:33,245
THEY ARRANGED FOR FRANK
TO FLY TO ODESSA

90
00:03:33,281 --> 00:03:35,181
TO MEET WITH
PROSPECTIVE BRIDES.

91
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:37,385
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
WEDDING BELLS.

92
00:03:37,418 --> 00:03:41,458
BUT FRANK HAS TO COME HOME WHILE
THEY WAIT FOR OLENA'S VISA.

93
00:03:41,489 --> 00:03:43,259
IMMIGRATION PROBLEMS.

94
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:44,461
THEN HE GETS A CALL
FROM HER BROKER

95
00:03:44,492 --> 00:03:46,362
SAYING IT'S GONNA BE
ANOTHER 100 GRAND

96
00:03:46,394 --> 00:03:47,564
TO GET OLENA
INTO THE STATES.

97
00:03:47,595 --> 00:03:50,195
NOW, FRANK DOESN'T HAVE
THAT KIND OF CASH.

98
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,400
SO THEN THE BROKER OFFERS HIM
ALTERNATIVE FINANCING.

99
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:54,403
CODE FOR "LOAN SHARK."

100
00:03:54,435 --> 00:03:55,495
EXACTLY.

101
00:03:55,536 --> 00:03:57,236
SO FRANK
GETS HIS NEW BRIDE,

102
00:03:57,271 --> 00:03:58,541
BUT HE CAN'T KEEP UP
WITH THE PAYMENTS.

103
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,472
SO THEN THE LOAN SHARK
TELLS HIM

104
00:04:00,508 --> 00:04:03,508
THAT THEY'RE GOING
TO TAKE OLENA AND MAKE
HER WORK OFF THE DEBT.

105
00:04:03,544 --> 00:04:06,384
I'M GUESSING WE'RE NOT TALKING
ABOUT A NICE OFFICE JOB.

106
00:04:06,414 --> 00:04:08,224
[ CHUCKLES ]
ALEXEI TUPELOV.

107
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,548
SUSPECTED OF RUNNING
THE LARGEST

108
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:13,393
PROSTITUTION AND LOAN-SHARKING
OPERATIONS IN THE MIDWEST.

109
00:04:13,421 --> 00:04:16,391
THE BUREAU'S BEEN TRYING TO NAIL
THIS GUY FOR YEARS,

110
00:04:16,424 --> 00:04:18,234
BUT NO ONE WILL TESTIFY.

111
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:21,428
HE ALSO HAPPENS TO OWN
EASTERN BLOC INTRODUCTIONS.

112
00:04:21,462 --> 00:04:23,562
SO IT'S A FRONT COMYEAH.

113
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:26,427
WE THINK THAT THE LOAN SHARK'S
ONE OF TUPELOV'S BOYS,

114
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:28,537
AND LAST NIGHT HE MADE GOOD
ON HIS THREAT.

115
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:30,499
FRANK COMES HOME,
SEES A BLUE CAMARO

116
00:04:30,538 --> 00:04:32,538
PARKED RIGHT OUTSIDE
HIS HOUSE.

117
00:04:32,573 --> 00:04:34,583
HE GOES INSIDE.
THERE'S AN INTRUDER.

118
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:36,308
THEY FIGHT.

119
00:04:36,344 --> 00:04:38,414
THE GUY SMASHES FRANK
OVER THE HEAD WITH A LAMP.

120
00:04:38,446 --> 00:04:41,246
THE LIVE-IN MAID
COMES HOME FROM HER NIGHT OFF,

121
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:42,421
FINDS FRANK UNCONSCIOUS,

122
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:44,590
CALLS THE COPS,
BUT OLENA IS ALREADY GONE.

123
00:04:44,618 --> 00:04:46,518
[ SCOFFS ] POOR GIRL.

124
00:04:46,554 --> 00:04:48,424
YEAH.

125
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,463
HOW CAN I HELP?

126
00:04:51,492 --> 00:04:53,262
HERE'S THE THING.

127
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,463
FRANK CAN'T GIVE US
A DESCRIPTION OF THIS GUY,

128
00:04:55,496 --> 00:04:57,596
EVEN THOUGH
THEY WERE FACE TO FACE.

129
00:04:57,631 --> 00:05:00,301
WELL, YOU SAID THE INTRUDER
HIT HIM OVER THE HEAD.

130
00:05:00,334 --> 00:05:01,604
THAT COULD CERTAINLY
AFFECT HIS MEMORY.

131
00:05:01,635 --> 00:05:03,465
THAT'S WHY
I BROUGHT THIS TO YOU.

132
00:05:03,504 --> 00:05:04,574
FRANK'S MEMORY IS FINE.

133
00:05:04,605 --> 00:05:06,465
HE CAN DESCRIBE
EVERYTHING

134
00:05:06,507 --> 00:05:08,437
THAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT
IN PERFECT DETAIL,

135
00:05:08,476 --> 00:05:11,306
SO HOW IS IT THAT HE CAN'T TELL
US WHAT THIS GUY LOOKED LIKE?

136
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,320
[ BEEPING ]

137
00:05:24,592 --> 00:05:26,332
WHAT THE [BLEEP]
IS THAT THING?

138
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,330
WHOLE-BODY-IMAGING
SCANNER.

139
00:05:28,362 --> 00:05:29,662
IT WASN'T HERE
LAST TIME.

140
00:05:29,697 --> 00:05:34,367
YEAH. NEW SECURITY PROTOCOLS.
I'LL MEET YOU ON THE OTHER SIDE.

141
00:05:34,402 --> 00:05:36,442
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

142
00:05:36,470 --> 00:05:38,670
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

143
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,390
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

144
00:06:03,564 --> 00:06:06,574
[ BEEPING INTENSIFIES ]

145
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,606
DANIEL!
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

146
00:06:18,646 --> 00:06:20,646
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA THE
HEALTH RISKS THOSE THINGS POSE?

147
00:06:20,681 --> 00:06:22,681
WH-- THAT?
THAT'S PERFECTLY SAFE.

148
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:24,686
According to who?
Some government regulatory body?

149
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:27,388
Like I really trust Uncle Sam
to look out for my well-being.

150
00:06:27,421 --> 00:06:29,491
OKAY, LISTEN, WHAT EXACTLY IS IT
THAT YOU'RE AFRAID OF?

151
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:32,563
SKIN CANCER, THYROID DISEASE,
MUTATED SPERM.

152
00:06:32,593 --> 00:06:34,363
M-MUTATED SPERM?

153
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:35,564
NOT TO MENTION
THE VIOLATION OF PRIVACY.

154
00:06:35,596 --> 00:06:37,396
I'M NOT ABOUT TO LET
SOME $10-AN-HOUR RENT-A-COP

155
00:06:37,431 --> 00:06:38,571
CHECK OUT
MY TESTICULAR REGION.

156
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:41,503
OKAY.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

157
00:06:41,535 --> 00:06:43,565
WE'RE GONNA DO THIS
THE OLD-FASHIONED WAY.

158
00:06:47,708 --> 00:06:49,778
YOU'RE REALLY ENJOYING THIS,
AREN'T YOU?

159
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,450
MR. PRENTICE,
YOU TOLD THE POLICE

160
00:06:54,482 --> 00:06:55,722
THAT YOU STRUGGLED
WITH THE INTRUDER
FOR MORE THAN A MINUTE,

161
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:58,389
THAT YOU WERE FACE-TO-FACE
THE WHOLE TIME.

162
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:00,518
ANY DISTINGUISHING FEATURES
OR CHARACTERISTICS?

163
00:07:00,554 --> 00:07:02,694
WELL, I TOLD THEM I'VE NEVER
BEEN TOO GOOD WITH FACES.

164
00:07:02,723 --> 00:07:06,393
THE INTRUDER -- WAS IT THE SAME
MAN YOU'VE BEEN PAYING OFF?

165
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:08,656
MAYBE. WELL, THEY WERE
ABOUT THE SAME SIZE.

166
00:07:08,696 --> 00:07:10,726
BUT THE GUY
THAT SHAKES ME DOWN

167
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:12,674
USUALLY WEARS ONE OF THOSE
ORTHODOX CROSSES --

168
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,470
A GOLD ONE ON A CHAIN
AROUND HIS NECK.

169
00:07:15,803 --> 00:07:18,713
WHAT DOES YOUR WIFE
LOOK LIKE?

170
00:07:19,707 --> 00:07:21,477
YOU GOT PICTURES OF HER.

171
00:07:21,509 --> 00:07:22,709
WHAT DOES SHE LOOK LIKE
TO YOU?

172
00:07:22,743 --> 00:07:26,483
BLOND, GOOD-LOOKING.

173
00:07:26,514 --> 00:07:27,754
SHE GOT A GOOD BODY.

174
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:30,481
D-DO YOU REALLY THINK I'M GONNA
SPEND ALL THAT MONEY

175
00:07:30,518 --> 00:07:32,488
TO BRING HER OVER HERE
IF SHE'S NOT HOT?

176
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,420
THE HUSBAND'S
A REAL CHARMER.

177
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,424
WE FIND THIS GIRL,
AND THEN WHAT?

178
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,756
SHE HAS TO GO BACK
TO THAT?

179
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,431
HERE.
PUT THIS ON.

180
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:40,629
JUST DO IT.

181
00:07:40,661 --> 00:07:41,631
OKAY.

182
00:07:41,662 --> 00:07:43,602
AND TAKE THESE.

183
00:07:43,631 --> 00:07:45,571
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF AN INTERROGATION.

184
00:07:45,599 --> 00:07:47,429
GO WITH ME ON THIS.

185
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:51,637
NOW, LET'S DO SOMETHING
ABOUT THAT HAIR.

186
00:07:55,643 --> 00:07:58,713
FRANK, THIS IS MISS JONES.
SHE'S A SKETCH ARTIST.

187
00:07:58,746 --> 00:08:00,506
SHE'S GONNA COME UP
WITH A COMPOSITE

188
00:08:00,548 --> 00:08:02,448
OF THE MAN
WHO ATTACKED YOU.

189
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:04,482
I SURE AS [BLEEP] HOPE YOU'RE
MORE HELP THAN THAT LAST GIRL.

190
00:08:06,687 --> 00:08:08,787
YOU DON'T RECOGNIZE HER?

191
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:09,792
WHY?

192
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,763
HAVE WE MET?

193
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:22,939
IT'S A SENSORY IMPAIRMENT
CALLED PROSOPAGNOSIA,

194
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:24,910
ALSO KNOWN AS
"FACE BLINDNESS."

195
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:26,138
EVEN THOUGH FRANK'S VISION
IS PERFECTLY NORMAL,

196
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:28,013
HE CAN'T RECOGNIZE FACES.

197
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,941
HE PROBABLY COULDN'T PICK
HIS OWN MOTHER OUT OF A LINEUP.

198
00:08:29,977 --> 00:08:31,137
BECAUSE OF THE BLOW
TO THE HEAD?

199
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:33,808
IT CAN BE CAUSED BY DAMAGE
TO THE FUSIFORM GYRUS,

200
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,847
BUT FRANK SAID HE'D NEVER
BEEN GOOD WITH FACES,

201
00:08:35,883 --> 00:08:37,153
WHICH MEANS
IT'S PROBABLY CONGENITAL.

202
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:39,054
WAIT A SECOND.

203
00:08:39,086 --> 00:08:40,986
THIS GUY'S HAD THIS BIZARRO
CONDITION HIS ENTIRE LIFE,

204
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:41,961
AND HE DOESN'T KNOW IT?

205
00:08:41,989 --> 00:08:43,819
HOW'S THAT EVEN POSSIBLE?

206
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:45,987
MOST PROSOPAGNOSIACS DEVELOP
UNCONSCIOUS STRATEGIES

207
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:48,026
FOR RECOGNIZING
THE PEOPLE THEY KNOW --

208
00:08:48,061 --> 00:08:51,101
THE WAY THEY DRESS, THE CONTEXT
THEY SEE THEM IN, THEIR VOICE.

209
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:53,966
GREAT.

210
00:08:54,001 --> 00:08:55,841
WELL, ACCORDING
TO FRANK'S STATEMENT,

211
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,839
THE INTRUDER NEVER SPOKE,
SO EVEN IF WE FIND THE GUY,

212
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:59,871
OUR WITNESS
CAN'T I.D. HIM.

213
00:08:59,907 --> 00:09:02,937
FRANK SPOKE TO THE LOAN SHARK
AT LEAST HALF A DOZEN TIMES.

214
00:09:02,976 --> 00:09:04,946
HE'D BE ABLE TO RECOGNIZE
HIS VOICE.

215
00:09:04,978 --> 00:09:08,018
WE FIND THE LOAN SHARK, GET
DANIEL TO HELP FRANK I.D. HIM.

216
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:11,018
WE GRILL HIS SORRY [BLEEP] UNTIL
HE TELLS US WHERE OLENA IS.

217
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,851
CAN I GO NOW?

218
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,216
FRANK COULDN'T PICK ANYBODY
OUT OF THE PHOTO ARRAY.

219
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:16,994
HOW DO WE KNOW WHICH ONE
OF TUPELOV'S GUYS TO HAUL IN?

220
00:09:19,026 --> 00:09:21,896
HOW ABOUT WE DROP OFF DANIEL
BACK AT CAMPUS

221
00:09:21,929 --> 00:09:23,129
AND GO FIND YOU A WIFE?

222
00:09:25,132 --> 00:09:29,102
WE KNOW THAT YOUR COMPANY
IS A FRONT FOR ALEXEI TUPELOV.

223
00:09:29,136 --> 00:09:32,036
[ Slavic accent ]
HE'S AN INVESTOR. SO?

224
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,882
SO, YOU TWO ARE RUNNING
QUITE A SCAM --

225
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:36,878
